    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - MULTIPLEXING (DATA LINKS) - 1708 DATA LINK
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x082526">
        <title>1708 DATA LINK</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTION</title>
            <figure id="f0825208" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0825208.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="368px"/>
                <caption>Typical 1708 Data Link Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ENGINE CONTROLLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TRANSMISSION CONTROLLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DIAGNOSTIC CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ABS CONTROLLER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0825208">1708 data link</hotlnk>
                is a twisted pair of wires. This data link connects the diagnostic connector, engine controller,
                transmission controller, air or hydraulic ABS controller as required. The primary purpose of this data
                link is to provide an electronic service tool the capability to program and diagnose the electrical
                controllers.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
